 The maiden edition of the Acting Vice Chancellor for One Day Initiative has been held at Caleb University, Imota, Lagos. It was introduced by the Vice Chancellor, Prof. Nosa Owens-Ibie, for members of the pioneer set of Caleb University Graduate Development Scheme, to serve as school head for one day. A statement by Head of Media and Public Relations Elvis Otobo, said Mrs Chiamaka Joyce Ehizenagah, assistant lecturer in the Department of Microbiology and Biotechnology, became the first acting vice chancellor. Mrs Ehizenagah presided over the presentation by officials from Lagos State University (LASU) and was introduced to a team from Lagos State Ministry of Science and Technology. She spoke at the inauguration of senate’s Business Committee,  met with deans, departmental heads,  and students’ representatives before debriefing Prof Owens-Ibie. She described the experience as unforgettable. “This indeed has impacted positively on my managerial experience, and l remain grateful to the institution for the opportunity to act as One-Day Vice Chancellor,” she said.